# Copy to .env for LOCAL runs only (e.g. running scripts/get-refresh-token.js).
# In production, these live as GitHub Actions repo secrets — never commit a real .env.

# No paid API keys needed for script/topic generation, images, or video
# backgrounds - this pipeline is fully open-source/self-hosted or free-tier:
#   - Script/topic generation: a local Ollama server (OLLAMA_URL/OLLAMA_MODEL
#     below, defaults to http://127.0.0.1:11434 and llama3.2). Install Ollama
#     and `ollama pull llama3.2` before running locally.
#   - Stock footage backgrounds (channels with "visualStyle": "stockFootage"):
#     PEXELS_API_KEY - a free registered key from https://www.pexels.com/api/
#     (no paid tier, same idea as the YouTube Data API key below).
#   - Illustrated images (channels with "visualStyle": "illustrated"):
#     SD_CPP_BIN / SD_CPP_MODEL point at a stable-diffusion.cpp binary and a
#     GGUF model - see backend/README.md for the local dev setup.
# OLLAMA_URL=http://127.0.0.1:11434
# OLLAMA_MODEL=llama3.2
# PEXELS_API_KEY=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# SD_CPP_BIN=/path/to/sd-cli
# SD_CPP_MODEL=/path/to/stable-diffusion-v1-5-Q8_0.gguf

# Google Cloud OAuth client (Desktop app type), shared across channels
YT_CLIENT_ID=xxxxxxxxxxxx.apps.googleusercontent.com
YT_CLIENT_SECRET=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# One refresh token per channel, obtained via `npm run get-token`
YT_REFRESH_TOKEN_CHANNEL1=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
YT_REFRESH_TOKEN_CHANNEL2=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
